   "source": [
    "# Truss element Response"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Supported truss elements include most truss elements in OpenSees, including:\n",
    "\n",
    "- ✅ Truss\n",
    "- ✅ TrussSection\n",
    "- ✅ corotTruss\n",
    "- ✅ corotTrussSection"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-11-22T02:28:25.949371Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2024-11-22T02:28:25.948371Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2024-11-22T02:28:27.619141Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-11-22T02:28:27.618197Z",
     "shell.execute_reply.started": "2024-11-22T02:28:25.949371Z"
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import openseespy.opensees as ops\n",
    "\n",
    "import opstool as opst\n",
    "\n",
    "%matplotlib inline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-11-22T02:28:27.620145Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2024-11-22T02:28:27.619141Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.331575Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.330569Z",
     "shell.execute_reply.started": "2024-11-22T02:28:27.620145Z"
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ops.wipe()\n",
    "ops.model(\"basic\", \"-ndm\", 2, \"-ndf\", 2)\n",
    "# variables\n",
    "A = 4.0\n",
    "E = 29000.0\n",
    "alpha = 0.05\n",
    "sY = 36.0\n",
    "udisp = 2.5\n",
    "Nsteps = 1000\n",
    "Px = 160.0\n",
    "Py = 0.0\n",
    "# create nodes\n",
    "ops.node(1, 0.0, 0.0)\n",
    "ops.node(2, 72.0, 0.0)\n",
    "ops.node(3, 168.0, 0.0)\n",
    "ops.node(4, 48.0, 144.0)\n",
    "# set boundary condition\n",
    "ops.fix(1, 1, 1)\n",
    "ops.fix(2, 1, 1)\n",
    "ops.fix(3, 1, 1)\n",
    "# define materials\n",
    "ops.uniaxialMaterial(\"Hardening\", 1, E, sY, 0.0, alpha / (1 - alpha) * E)\n",
    "# define elements\n",
    "ops.element(\"Truss\", 1, 1, 4, A, 1)\n",
    "ops.element(\"Truss\", 2, 2, 4, A, 1)\n",
    "ops.element(\"Truss\", 3, 3, 4, A, 1)\n",
    "# create TimeSeries\n",
    "ops.timeSeries(\"Linear\", 1)\n",
    "# create a plain load pattern\n",
    "ops.pattern(\"Plain\", 1, 1)\n",
    "# Create the nodal load\n",
    "ops.load(4, Px, Py)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",

    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# plot\n",
    "opst.vis.pyvista.set_plot_props(notebook=True)  # Set notebook mode for PyVista\n",
    "fig = opst.vis.pyvista.plot_model(show_nodal_loads=True, load_scale=3, bc_scale=5)\n",
    "fig.show(jupyter_backend=\"static\")  # or None"
   ]
  },

   "metadata": {

    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "## Result Saving"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.333575Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.333575Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.343019Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.342010Z",
     "shell.execute_reply.started": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.333575Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ops.system(\"BandGeneral\")\n",
    "ops.constraints(\"Transformation\")\n",
    "ops.numberer(\"RCM\")\n",
    "ops.test(\"NormDispIncr\", 1.0e-12, 10, 3)\n",
    "ops.algorithm(\"Newton\")\n",
    "ops.integrator(\"LoadControl\", 1.0 / Nsteps)\n",
    "ops.analysis(\"Static\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "raw_mimetype": "text/restructuredtext",
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "``opstool`` allows us to save the data at each step of the analysis!\n",
    "First, we create a database class using :class:`opstool.post.CreateODB`, and then, during each step of the analysis, we call its method ``.fetch_response_step`` to retrieve the data for the current step. \n",
    "Once all the analysis steps are completed, we use the ``.save_response`` method to save the data in one go."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.346023Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.345024Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.765613Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.765613Z",
     "shell.execute_reply.started": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.346023Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<pre style=\"white-space:pre;overflow-x:auto;line-height:normal;font-family:Menlo,'DejaVu Sans Mono',consolas,'Courier New',monospace\"><span style=\"color: #cf6275; text-decoration-color: #cf6275; font-weight: bold\">OPSTOOL™</span> <span style=\"color: #12e193; text-decoration-color: #12e193; font-weight: bold\">::</span>  All responses data with _odb_tag = <span style=\"color: #008080; text-decoration-color: #008080; font-weight: bold\">1</span> saved in \n",
       "<span style=\"color: #ffc168; text-decoration-color: #ffc168; font-weight: bold\">g:\\opstool\\docs\\src\\post\\.opstool.output\\RespStepData-</span><span style=\"color: #ffc168; text-decoration-color: #ffc168; font-weight: bold\">1.</span><span style=\"color: #ffc168; text-decoration-color: #ffc168; font-weight: bold\">odb</span>!\n",
       "</pre>\n"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "\u001b[1;38;2;207;98;117mOPSTOOL™\u001b[0m \u001b[1;38;2;18;225;147m::\u001b[0m  All responses data with _odb_tag = \u001b[1;36m1\u001b[0m saved in \n",
       "\u001b[1;38;2;255;193;104mg:\\opstool\\docs\\src\\post\\.opstool.output\\RespStepData-\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;255;193;104m1.\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;255;193;104modb\u001b[0m!\n"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ODB = opst.post.CreateODB(odb_tag=1)\n",
    "for i in range(Nsteps):\n",
    "    ops.analyze(1)\n",
    "    ODB.fetch_response_step()\n",
    "ODB.save_response()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Result Reading"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "raw_mimetype": "text/restructuredtext",

   },
   "source": [
    "The provided function :func:`opstool.post.get_element_responses` make it easy to read element responses.\n",
    "\n",
    "``ele_type=\"Truss\"`` is used to specify extracting the response of frame elements."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "ele_type: Truss\n",
      "Available Response Types (resp_type):\n",
      "  - axialForce\n",
      "    resp_dim: ['time', 'eleTags']\n",
      "    resp_dof: None\n",
      "  - axialDefo\n",
      "    resp_dim: ['time', 'eleTags']\n",
      "    resp_dof: None\n",
      "  - Stress\n",
      "    resp_dim: ['time', 'eleTags']\n",
      "    resp_dof: None\n",
      "  - Strain\n",
      "    resp_dim: ['time', 'eleTags']\n",
      "    resp_dof: None\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "info = opst.post.get_element_responses_info(ele_type=\"Truss\")"
   ]
  },
